field_data.Author: Scott
field_data.Sample Name: Reshma4E waas sputtered last month at 400 C in 16(O), Easter1B was sputtered at RT 19D19 in (18)O

notes: an adaptor from swagelok for the carrier gas inlet. Chip is the non-aqueous chip that the interface block came with. Jump during CP at 450 s indicates CV has become tilty. And, when it scans again, indeed it has. Holding at 1.25 V vs RHE for dose of CO. --- Reshma4E --- 01... Beautiful, no exchange (link1) (2.00e-12 - 3.5e-13) / (4.15e-10 - 0) = 1.65e-2/4.15 = 0.398% is natural ratio! Less than a microamp of COox, Can't really see any m/z=46 --- Easter1A --- 02... Beautiful, exchange! 20 minutes. Both a transient excess and a bit of steady state! Also, incredibly steady signals. link2 No attempt on this sample to isolate the transient, but ready for next sample. About a microamp of COox, can't really see any m/z=46. Extraction doesn't seem worth it on this sample. -- Easter1B 03... Beautiful, same amount of exchange as Easter1A. Potential goes up then comes down. Hm... Each time I flow a bit to withdraw electrolyte, m/z=34 to m/z=32 ratio converges to the natural ratio!
